A web application designed to connect job seekers in Kenya's informal sector with potential employers. 
Kazi hub aims to provide a platform for people seeking informal work opportunities—such as manual labor, 
domestic work, and other essential services—to find jobs easily and reliably, 
helping to bridge the gap between employers and the skilled, 
unskilled, or semi-skilled workforce in Ken

Features
User Registration and Authentication: Secure sign-up and login for both job seekers and employers.


Job Listings: Employers can post available jobs, specifying required skills, location, and compensation.

Search and Filtering: Job seekers can search for jobs based on location, job type, and pay range.

Profile Management: Both job seekers and employers can create and manage detailed profiles.

Job Applications: Job seekers can apply for jobs and communicate with employers directly.

Real-Time Notifications: Notifications for job applications, approvals, and other important events.

Admin Dashboard: Admin users have access to a dashboard to manage users, jobs, and overall app activity.

Tech Stack
Backend: Django (Python)
Frontend: HTML, CSS, JavaScript, Django Templates
Database: SQLite (for development), PostgreSQL/MySQL (for production)
Hosting: Heroku/AWS/Any preferred cloud service
Version Control: Git and GitHub

